---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import AceArt from "../components/AceArt.astro";

const description =
  "ACE Engine: an early PTL research tool for auditable allocation analysis from scheduler and telemetry traces.";
---

<BaseLayout title="ACE Engine | Plain Theory Labs" description={description}>
  <section class="section prose">
    <h1>ACE Engine</h1>

    <div class="visual-center" aria-hidden="true">
      <AceArt />
    </div>
    <p class="figure-caption muted">ACE is an early engine for turning traces into readable structure.</p>

    <p>
      ACE is an early research tool that reads scheduler and telemetry traces, then produces a report with review
      queues so teams can inspect what changed and compare runs over time.
    </p>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <h2>A quick example</h2>
    <pre class="report-excerpt"><code>$ ace analyze --input jobs.csv --mode msa --safety-mode basic --json-out out.json
jobs_analyzed: 12840
allocation_changes: 918
risk_flag_jobs: 4861
review_queue_near_zero: 2132
review_queue_over_requested: 671
capacity_savings_usd: 18374.42
report_written: out.json</code></pre>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <h2>The math</h2>
    <h3>1) Utilization summary (per job)</h3>
    <pre class="formula-block"><code>util_avg = mean(utilization_samples)
util_p95 = percentile(utilization_samples, 95)</code></pre>

    <h3>2) Over-request heuristic (conceptual)</h3>
    <pre class="formula-block"><code>over_request_ratio = requested / max(observed, epsilon)</code></pre>

    <h3>3) Review score (weighted heuristic)</h3>
    <pre class="formula-block"><code>score = w1*(1 - util_avg) + w2*log1p(requested) + w3*variance(runtime)</code></pre>

    <p>
      These formulas are heuristics under active research. They prioritize human review and are not automatic control
      logic.
    </p>

    <p class="inline-links">
      <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
